originalText.text: Absolute worst parking location in NYC.  It seems almost as if it is a scam.  I paid over $100 for reservations WEEKS in advance.  Drove over 4 hours to NYC.  Once I arrived, I pulled in and was greeted by one of the rudest people I have ever came into contact with in my entire life.  Before I could even get a word out the man said "there's no room".  I told him how I had a reservation and he shrugged his shoulders, saying "well you're not parking here".  He told me how I can TRY to get my money back online.  As I am not from around the NYC area, I asked if he knew of any other options nearby where I could park, and his response was "Somewhere else".  This place needs some serious help.  Not sure if they're lacking a quality manager, or if the attendants just didn't get any education in their life and can't count how many cars they can let in while considering the amount of reservations they have.  Getting my money back was no easy task either.  They wanted proof that I had to park at a different location, pictures of bank transactions, pictures of the full sign outside of the garage(which there was none).  Do yourself a favor and park your car literally anywhere else in the city.  This place is run by idiots and if they have room for your car, they'll most definitely damage it.

originalText.text: Parked an SUV here for about 48 hours (Wednesday evening - Friday evening). We had no issues. Paid through SpotHero including the oversize vehicle fee. Quick drop off and pick up.

originalText.text: My friend was doing a recording at the Dimena Canter, and to help him out, I took his car to Laz nearby.  As I approached, a car was trying to exit the garage from the entrance lane.  With cars behind me and to my left and right, I could not reverse.  I waved at the driver and gestured to him to exit from the appropriate lane.  He nodded, and we coordinated.  That moment a Laz attendant came running out and yelled at me to wait in the street.  Did he not see the cars?  He continued to berate me as I pulled in.   I explained, no change in his behavior.  And, no apology to a paying customer.  Was he rude because I am a woman?  If I had been parking my own car, I would have left immediately.  Never giving my business to this company.
